<inglise> DIRECTIVE 98/84/EC OF THE EUROPEAN PARLIAMENT AND OF THE COUNCIL of 20 November 1998 on the legal protection of services based on, or consisting of, conditional access </inglise>
<eesti> EUROOPA PARLAMENDI JA N&Otilde;UKOGU DIREKTIIV 98/84/E&Uuml; tingimusjuurdep&auml;&auml;sul p&otilde;hinevate v&otilde;i seda sisaldavate teenuste &otilde;iguskaitse kohta 20. november 1998 </eesti>
<inglise> THE EUROPEAN PARLIAMENT AND THE COUNCIL OF THE EUROPEAN UNION, </inglise>
<eesti> EUROOPA PARLAMENT JA EUROOPA LIIDU N&Otilde;UKOGU, </eesti>
<inglise> Having regard to the Treaty establishing the European Community, and in particular Articles 57(2), 66 and 100a thereof, </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;ttes arvesse Euroopa &Uuml;henduse asutamislepingut, eriti selle artikli 57 l&otilde;iget 2 ning artikleid 66 ja 100a, </eesti>
<inglise> Having regard to the proposal from the Commission (1), </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;ttes arvesse komisjoni ettepanekut, (1) </eesti>
<inglise> Having regard to the opinion of the Economic and Social Committee (2), </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;ttes arvesse majandus- ja sotsiaalkomitee arvamust, (2) </eesti>
<inglise> Acting in accordance with the procedure laid down in Article 189b of the Treaty (3), </inglise>
<eesti> tegutsedes asutamislepingu artiklis 189b etten&auml;htud menetluse kohaselt (3) </eesti>
<inglise> (1) Whereas the objectives of the Community as laid down in the Treaty include creating an ever closer union among the peoples of Europe and ensuring economic and social progress, by eliminating the barriers which divide them; </inglise>
<eesti> ning arvestades, et: 1) &uuml;henduse asutamislepingus s&auml;testatud eesm&auml;rkide hulka kuulub j&auml;rjest tihedama liidu loomine Euroopa rahvaste vahel ning majandusliku ja &uuml;hiskondliku arengu tagamine neid lahutavate t&otilde;kete k&otilde;rvaldamise teel; </eesti>
<inglise> (2) Whereas the cross-border provision of broadcasting and information society services may contribute, from the individual point of view, to the full effectiveness of freedom of expression as a fundamental right and, from the collective point of view, to the achievement of the objectives laid down in the Treaty; </inglise>
<eesti> 2) ringh&auml;&auml;lingu- ja info&uuml;hiskonna teenuste piiri&uuml;lene pakkumine v&otilde;ib &uuml;ksikisiku vaatepunktist l&auml;htudes kaasa aidata s&otilde;navabaduse kui p&otilde;hi&otilde;iguse t&auml;ielikule saavutamisele ja kollektiivsest vaatepunktist l&auml;htudes asutamislepingus seatud eesm&auml;rkideni j&otilde;udmisele; </eesti>
<inglise> (3) Whereas the Treaty provides for the free movement of all services which are normally provided for remuneration; whereas this right, as applied to broadcasting and information society services, is also a specific manifestation in Community law of a more general principle, namely freedom of expression as enshrined in Article 10 of the European Convention for the Protection of Human Rights and Fundamental Freedoms; whereas that Article explicitly recognizes the right of citizens to receive and impart information regardless of frontiers and whereas any restriction of that right must be based on due consideration of other legitimate interests deserving of legal protection; </inglise>
<eesti> 3) asutamisleping n&auml;eb ette k&otilde;igi tavaliselt tasu eest pakutavate teenuste vaba liikumise; ringh&auml;&auml;lingu- ja info&uuml;hiskonna teenuste suhtes kohaldatuna t&auml;hendab see &otilde;igus samuti &uuml;henduse &otilde;iguse &uuml;ldisema p&otilde;him&otilde;tte, nimelt s&otilde;navabaduse erivormi, mis sisaldub inim&otilde;iguste ja p&otilde;hivabaduste kaitse Euroopa konventsiooni artiklis 10; see artikkel tunnustab s&otilde;naselgelt kodanike &otilde;igust saada ja edastada teavet hoolimata piiridest ja k&otilde;ik selle &otilde;iguse piirangud peavad p&otilde;hinema muude &otilde;iguskaitset v&auml;&auml;rivate seaduslike huvide vajalikul arvessev&otilde;tmisel; </eesti>
<inglise> (4) Whereas the Commission undertook a wide-ranging consultation based on the Green Paper 'Legal Protection of Encrypted Services in the Internal Market'; whereas the results of that consultation confirmed the need for a Community legal instrument ensuring the legal protection of all those services whose remuneration relies on conditional access; </inglise>
<eesti> 4) komisjon korraldas laiaulatusliku n&otilde;upidamise, mis p&otilde;hines rohelisel raamatul "Kodeeritud teenuste &otilde;iguskaitse siseturul"; selle n&otilde;upidamise tulemused kinnitasid vajadust &uuml;henduse &otilde;igusakti j&auml;rele, mis tagaks &otilde;iguskaitse k&otilde;igile nendele teenustele, mille tasu s&otilde;ltub tingimusjuurdep&auml;&auml;sust; </eesti>
<inglise> (5) Whereas the European Parliament, in its Resolution of 13 May 1997 on the Green Paper (4), called on the Commission to present a proposal for a Directive covering all encoded services in respect of which encoding is used to ensure payment of a fee, and agreed that this should include information society services provided at a distance by electronic means and at the individual request of a service receiver, as well as broadcasting services; </inglise>
<eesti> 5) Euroopa Parlament palus oma rohelist raamatut k&auml;sitlevas 13. mai 1997. aasta resolutsioonis (4) komisjonil esitada ettepanek direktiivi kohta, mis h&otilde;lmaks k&otilde;iki kodeeritud teenuseid, mille puhul kodeeringut kasutatakse selleks, et tagada tasu maksmine, ja oli seisukohal, et see peaks h&otilde;lmama info&uuml;hiskonna teenuseid, mida pakutakse vahemaa tagant elektroonilisel teel ja teenusesaaja isikliku taotluse p&otilde;hjal, samuti ringh&auml;&auml;linguteenuseid; </eesti>
<inglise> (6) Whereas the opportunities offered by digital technologies provide the potential for increasing consumer choice and contributing to cultural pluralism, by developing an even wider range of services within the meaning of Articles 59 and 60 of the Treaty; whereas the viability of those services will often depend on the use of conditional access in order to obtain the remuneration of the service provider; whereas, accordingly, the legal protection of service providers against illicit devices which allow access to these services free of charge seems necessary in order to ensure the economic viability of the services; </inglise>
<eesti> 6) digitaaltehnoloogiate pakutavad v&otilde;imalused laiendavad tarbija valikupotentsiaali ja edendavad kultuurilist pluralismi, arendades v&auml;lja j&auml;rjest laiema valiku teenuseid asutamislepingu artiklite 59 ja 60 t&auml;henduses; nende teenuste v&otilde;imalikkus s&otilde;ltub sageli tingimusjuurdep&auml;&auml;su kasutamisest, et teenuseosutaja saaks tasu; seet&otilde;ttu tundub nende teenuste majandusliku eluj&otilde;u huvides vajalik teenuseosutajate &otilde;iguskaitse ebaseaduslike seadmete vastu, mis v&otilde;imaldavad tasuta ligip&auml;&auml;su neile teenustele; </eesti>
<inglise> (7) Whereas the importance of this issue was recognized by the Commission Communication on 'A European Initiative in Electronic Commerce'; </inglise>
<eesti> 7) selle k&uuml;simuse t&auml;htsust tunnistas komisjon oma teatises "Euroopa algatus elektroonilises kaubanduses"; </eesti>
<inglise> (8) Whereas, in accordance with Article 7a of the Treaty, the internal market is to comprise an area without internal frontiers in which the free movement of services and goods is ensured; whereas Article 128(4) of the Treaty requires the Community to take cultural aspects into account in its action under other provisions of the Treaty; whereas by virtue of Article 130(3) of the Treaty, the Community must, through the policies and activities it pursues, contribute to creating the conditions necessary for the competitiveness of its industry; </inglise>
<eesti> 8) koosk&otilde;las asutamislepingu artikliga 7a k&auml;sitatakse siseturuna sisepiirideta ala, kus on tagatud teenuste ja kaupade vaba liikumine; Euroopa &Uuml;henduse asutamislepingu artikli 128 l&otilde;ige 4 n&auml;eb ette, et &uuml;hendus v&otilde;taks asutamislepingu s&auml;tete kohaselt tegutsemisel arvesse kultuuriaspekte; asutamislepingu artikli 130 l&otilde;ike 3 kohaselt peab &uuml;henduse poliitika ja tegevus kaasa aitama &uuml;henduse t&ouml;&ouml;stuse konkurentsiv&otilde;imelisuseks vajalike tingimuste loomisele; </eesti>
<inglise> (9) Whereas this Directive is without prejudice to possible future Community or national provisions meant to ensure that a number of broadcasting services, recognized as being of public interest, are not based on conditional access; </inglise>
<eesti> 9) k&auml;esolev direktiiv ei piira v&otilde;imalikke edasisi &uuml;henduse v&otilde;i siseriiklikke &otilde;igusnorme, mis on kavandatud tagama, et hulk &uuml;ldist huvi pakkuvaid ringh&auml;&auml;linguteenuseid ei p&otilde;hineks tingimusjuurdep&auml;&auml;sul; </eesti>
<inglise> (10) Whereas this Directive is without prejudice to the cultural aspects of any further Community action concerning new services; </inglise>
<eesti> 10) k&auml;esolev direktiiv ei piira mingite edasiste uusi teenuseid k&auml;sitlevate &uuml;henduse meetmete kultuuriaspekte; </eesti>
<inglise> (11) Whereas the disparity between national rules concerning the legal protection of services based on, or consisting of, conditional access is liable to create obstacles to the free movement of services and goods; </inglise>
<eesti> 11) erinevus tingimusjuurdep&auml;&auml;sul p&otilde;hinevate v&otilde;i seda sisaldavate teenuste &otilde;iguskaitset k&auml;sitlevate siseriiklike &otilde;igusaktide vahel tekitab t&otilde;en&auml;oliselt teenuste ja kaupade vabale liikumisele takistusi; </eesti>
<inglise> (12) Whereas the application of the Treaty is not sufficient to remove these internal market obstacles; whereas those obstacles should therefore be removed by providing for an equivalent level of protection between Member States; whereas this implies an approximation of the national rules relating to the commercial activities which concern illicit devices; </inglise>
<eesti> 12) asutamislepingu kohaldamisest ei piisa nende siseturu takistuste k&otilde;rvaldamiseks; seet&otilde;ttu tuleks need takistused k&otilde;rvaldada liikmesriikides v&otilde;rdv&auml;&auml;rse kaitsetaseme loomise teel; see eeldab, et &uuml;htlustataks siseriiklikud eeskirjad, mis k&auml;sitlevad &auml;ritegevust ebaseaduslike seadmetega; </eesti>
<inglise> (13) Whereas it seems necessary to ensure that Member States provide appropriate legal protection against the placing on the market, for direct or indirect financial gain, of an illicit device which enables or facilitates without authority the circumvention of any technological measures designed to protect the remuneration of a legally provided service; </inglise>
<eesti> 13) oluline oleks tagada, et liikmesriigid annavad n&otilde;uetekohase &otilde;iguskaitse selle vastu, et otsese v&otilde;i kaudse rahalise kasu nimel viiakse turule ebaseaduslik seade, mis v&otilde;imaldab v&otilde;i h&otilde;lbustab loata k&otilde;rvalehoidmist tehnoloogilistest meetmetest, mis on kavandatud selleks, et kaitsta seaduslikult pakutud teenuse tasu; </eesti>
<inglise> (14) Whereas those commercial activities which concern illicit devices include commercial communications covering all forms of advertising, direct marketing, sponsorship, sales promotion and public relations promoting such products and services; </inglise>
<eesti> 14) ebaseaduslike seadmetega seotud &auml;ritegevuse hulka kuulub kaubanduslik teave, mis k&auml;ib selliste toodete ja teenuste edendamise igasuguse reklaami, otseturustuse, sponsorluse, m&uuml;&uuml;gi edendamise ja avalike suhete kohta; </eesti>
<inglise> (15) Whereas those commercial activities are detrimental to consumers who are misled about the origin of illicit devices; whereas a high level of consumer protection is needed in order to fight against this kind of consumer fraud; whereas Article 129a(1) of the Treaty provides that the Community should contribute to the achievement of a high level of consumer protection by the measures it adopts pursuant to Article 100a thereof; </inglise>
<eesti> 15) see &auml;ritegevus on kahjulik tarbijatele, keda v&otilde;ib eksitada ebaseaduslike seadmete p&auml;ritolu; et v&otilde;idelda seda laadi tarbijate petmise vastu, on vaja k&otilde;rgetasemelist tarbijakaitset; asutamislepingu artikli 129a l&otilde;ige 1 n&auml;eb ette, et &uuml;hendus peaks kaasa aitama k&otilde;rgetasemelise tarbijakaitse tagamisele meetmetega, mida ta v&otilde;tab vastavalt lepingu artiklile 100a; </eesti>
<inglise> (16) Whereas, therefore, the legal framework for the creation of a single audiovisual area laid down in Council Directive 89/552/EEC of 3 October 1989 on the coordination of certain provisions laid down by law, regulation or administrative action in Member States concerning the pursuit of television broadcasting activities (5) should be supplemented with reference to conditional access techniques as laid down in this Directive, in order, not least, to ensure equal treatment of the suppliers of cross-border broadcasts, regardless of their place of establishment; </inglise>
<eesti> 16) seet&otilde;ttu peaks n&otilde;ukogu 3. oktoobri 1989. aasta direktiiviga 89/552/EM&Uuml; teleringh&auml;&auml;lingutegevust k&auml;sitlevate liikmesriikide teatavate &otilde;igusnormide koosk&otilde;lastamise kohta (5) etten&auml;htud &uuml;htse audiovisuaalse piirkonna loomise &otilde;iguslikku raamistikku t&auml;iendama viitega k&auml;esolevas direktiivis s&auml;testatud tingimusjuurdep&auml;&auml;sule, et tagada v&auml;hemalt piiri&uuml;lese levi pakkujate v&otilde;rdne kohtlemine nende asukohast hoolimata; </eesti>
<inglise> (17) Whereas, in accordance with the Council Resolution of 29 June 1995 on the effective uniform application of Community law and on the penalties applicable for breaches of Community law in the internal market (6), Member States are required to take action to ensure that Community law is duly applied with the same effectiveness and thoroughness as national law; </inglise>
<eesti> 17) vastavalt n&otilde;ukogu 29. juuni 1995. aasta resolutsioonile &uuml;henduse &otilde;iguse t&otilde;husa &uuml;htse kohaldamise ja siseturul &uuml;henduse &otilde;iguse rikkumise eest kohaldatavate karistuste kohta (6) peavad liikmesriigid v&otilde;tma meetmeid tagamaks, et &uuml;henduse &otilde;igust kohaldataks n&otilde;uetekohaselt sama t&otilde;husalt ja t&auml;ielikult kui siseriiklikku &otilde;igust; </eesti>
<inglise> (18) Whereas, in accordance with Article 5 of the Treaty, Member States are required to take all appropriate measures to guarantee the application and effectiveness of Community law, in particular by ensuring that the sanctions chosen are effective, dissuasive and proportionate and the remedies appropriate; </inglise>
<eesti> 18) vastavalt asutamislepingu artiklile 5 peavad liikmesriigid v&otilde;tma k&otilde;ik vajalikud meetmed, et tagada &uuml;henduse &otilde;iguse kohaldamine ja efektiivsus, eelk&otilde;ige kindlustada, et valitud sanktsioonid on t&otilde;husad, hoiatavad ja proportsionaalsed ning &otilde;iguskaitsevahendid asjakohased; </eesti>
<inglise> (19) Whereas the approximation of the laws, regulations and administrative provisions of the Member States should be limited to what is needed in order to achieve the objectives of the internal market, in accordance with the principle of proportionality as set out in the third paragraph of Article 3b of the Treaty; </inglise>
<eesti> 19) liikmesriikide &otilde;igusnormide &uuml;htlustamist tuleks piirata siseturu eesm&auml;rkide saavutamiseks vajalikuga vastavalt asutamislepingu artikli 3b kolmandas l&otilde;igus s&auml;testatud proportsionaalsuse p&otilde;him&otilde;ttele; </eesti>
<inglise> (20) Whereas the distribution of illicit devices includes transfer by any means and putting such devices on the market for circulation inside or outside the Community; </inglise>
